gomodel:SYNGO_1470  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 5: Impaired LTP but Intact LTD in DCCf/f,cre+ Mice. Floxed DCC mice crossed to CamKII-Cre mice show impaired LTP at CA3-CA1 synapses. Figure 6: Enhancing NMDAR function either by decreasing extracellular levels of Mg2+ or by pharmacologically activating Src completely rescued LTP in DCCf/f,cre+ mice. Authors conclude that DCC activation of Src is required for the induction of NMDAR-dependent LTP.. Experimental description: Methods: Floxed DCC mice were generated as previously described (Krimpenfort et al., 2012" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-29" ;
